        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li><strong>Zero permanent motor nerve injuries</strong> documented</li>
          <li><strong>&lt;2% transient weakness</strong> (all resolved)</li>
          <li><strong>&lt;1% hematoma</strong> requiring intervention</li>
          <li><strong>&lt;3% revision rate</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mb-6">
          These outcomes match or exceed published benchmarks for endoscopic midface procedures. The
          technique has been successfully taught to <strong>130+ surgeons</strong> who report similar
          results — validating that the approach is reproducible, not dependent on unique individual skill.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-6">
          The burden of proof, then, should fall on the more expensive, more complex approach to
          demonstrate <em>superior</em> outcomes that justify the additional cost and complexity. That
          evidence, for midface lifting specifically, is not compelling.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-primary-900">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif text-white mb-4">Learn Direct Vision Technique</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-primary-200 mb-8">
        ENDOMIDFACE® mentorship includes complete training in Direct Vision approach, anatomical
        mapping, and hands-on guidance.
